        "value": "Hospital Assessment (damaged, CEONC related equipment, service availability and need) using standard tools\r\n\tSupport CEONC equipment based on gaps and needs\r\n\tDevelop central level clinical mentors using Low dose high frequency (LDHF)\r\n\tMentoring coaching to health workers to refresh clinical skills\r\n\tPost disaster readiness, psychosocial support and running drills on key safety/emergency procedures to health workers\r\n\tSharing progress/update at RH cluster group meeting\r\n\tParticipate in DDRC meeting and share progress\r\n\tStrengthen and support Quality Assurance Working Group (QAWG) in the District\r\n\tCoordination with other agencies and donors regarding logistic management and support\r\n\tRespond to other FHD and RH cluster requests\r\n\tMonitoring and supervision by project central staff and government stakeholders\r\n\tProject evaluation and submission to SWC\r\n\tProject evaluation"
